      out.write("<Table class =\"table\"><tr><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"><h8>Objective</h8></td></tr><tr ><td>  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>To log the movement of documents/drawings of RVNL projects during approval stage and to provide a reporting system to monitor the progress of approvals and to ensure speedier approvals of project documents with ultimate objective of faster project delivery.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Features</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Logging movement of documents/drawings of RVNL projects while these are physically approved by Railway Officers at divisional and zonal HQ level. Also register movement of document sent to officers of other Organizations like NHAI, MCL, SECL etc.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Generate detailed and summary reports based on user selected filter criteria to assist in monitoring the position by higher Officials of Railways and RVNL. It is possible to set filters for selecting documents to be included in the report for a zone, division, project, status, document type,  submitted between dates, Railway user, Pending for days, Other Organization or any combination of these parameter. Reports can be further filtered dynamically with search criteria given on board.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Trigger automatic alerts/reminders (to be sent as email/sms) to concerned Railway officers to expedite approvals.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Send periodic alerts to DRM and GM with position of delayed documents automatically. </td></tr><tr ><td> 5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Develop long term statistics to help in decision making and framing up of policy guidelines/MOUs etc.</td></tr><tr ><td> 6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>In order to facilitate entry of documents which are already in the process of approval rather than starting only with new documents, system has been designed to allow entry of date (instead of capturing date and time of action automatically) for a particular action. This is more so as the documents will be moving physically for signatures and appropriate entries in the portal as per actual date of approval can be made by the officer later as per his convenience.</td></tr><tr ><td> 7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Setting automatic alerts/reminders to manual mode for a PIU has also been designed in the system at Local-Admin level.</td></tr><tr ><td> 8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Users will have controlled access to document and other details limited to their jurisdiction e.g. PIU level of RVNL user will have access to all documents of that PIU only and zonal HQ level Railway user will have access to all documents referred to any division of that zone including HQ. CO level users of RVNL and Railway Board level officers of Railways will have access to all documents belonging to any PIU of RVNL or pending with any division/zone.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >User Creation & Modification</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>System-Admin (CO level admin) & Local-Admin (PIU level admin) can create new Users (RVNL, MOR & other Organizations), but new Local-Admin can only be created by System-Admin.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Local-Admin cannot create another Local-Admin but it can create other users of Railway zones, which are under the jurisdiction of the PIU as earmarked by System-Admin while creating the Local-Admin for that PIU.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>One PIU can only have one Local-Admin.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>All the created information for any user of any zone/ organization can be updated & password can be reset by System-Admin.</td></tr><tr ><td> 5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>A Local-Admin can update information pertaining to users in its jurisdiction and also reset the password.</td></tr><tr ><td> 6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>User-Id for a user should be complete Designation along with place of posting without any space in between (For example-SrDEN/E/WAT) so that the User-Id is unique. User-Id should be written in proper letter (combination of capital/small) as is written in normal correspondence as this user Id will be used in all reports and mail alerts.</td></tr><tr ><td> 7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>DRM of division and GM of zone should invariably be created with complete details like email id and mobile numbers as weekly positions of delayed documents shall be sent by email/SMS to the Railway users automatically by the system.  </td></tr><tr ><td> 8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Correct email id and mobile numbers should be entered as alerts and reminders will be sent to all Railway users. In case of change of email /mobile of a user, the details should be modified accordingly by Local-Admin of that PIU or System-Admin.</td></tr><tr ><td> 9)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>RVNL Users:</b> Only users like CPM/SC, GM/S&T/SC and GM/Elec/SC should be created as these users will only be forwarding documents/drawings for approvals of Railway Users and alerts will be initiated from their side to such users, DRMs and GMs. </td></tr><tr ><td> 10)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Railway Users:</b> For division level users, only branch officer/JAG level users be created so that document is shown pending against his name in case it is pending with some officers/staff working under him. Normally, users required to approve/sign the document /drawing should be created. For HQ level users, only SAG level officers who normally sign such document be created.</td></tr><tr ><td> 11)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Users of Other Organizations:</b> In order to log the movement and for showing in reports, documents pending with users of organizations like NHAI, Forest, NTPC, MCL, SECL etc can also be created by local admin. Normally such users are created with organization name and user id only and no other details for such users are required to be filled as such users will not be using this portal. The RVNL user only will make entries for forwarding the document and registering receipt of approved document as and when it is approved by that user.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >User Jurisdiction and Role</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>The jurisdiction based access to documents and other details and also role of each user type will be as explained below;</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>System-Admin:</b> Will create/edit master data  and PIU level Local-Admins will be basic function. While creating/editing Local-Admin for a PIU, System-Admin will also assign Railway zones to that PIU. In addition, System-admin can also create/edit users and projects and reset user passwords, though these tasks shall normally be done by PIU level Local-Admins. Will have access to all documents and details available in the system.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Local-Admin:</b> Will create/edit users of PIU and Railway zones/divisions assigned to that PIU. Can reset passwords for users under its jurisdiction.  Can reset alert/reminders mode from Auto to Manual and vice-versa. Will have access to all documents and details of that PIU. Local-Admin can also add new Organizations in the master list while creating a user for this organization.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>RVNL User (PIU Level):</b> Will assign a project package to himself and then create documents for forwarding to Railway/Other organization Users. Jurisdiction of such users is limited to projects handled by the PIU, zones and divisions where their projects lie. They can view only documents and other details of their PIU only.</td></tr><tr ><td> 5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>RVNL User (Corporate Office level):</b> Will only monitor position and will be able to generate different types of reports. Will have access to all documents and details available in the system.</td></tr><tr ><td> <h8 >6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Railway User (Division level):</b> Will take action on each document forwarded to such users. They will either approve and forward to other Railway user or return the document back to RVNL with observations or approval. The documents can also be forwarded to other Railway user without approval. Will be able to generate different types of reports for documents lying in that division. Will have access to all documents and details pertaining to that division and PIU(s) interacting with the division. After approval of the document from all concerned divisional officers, document will be returned back to RVNL for submission to Zonal HQ (if required).</td></tr><tr ><td> 7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Railway User (Zonal HQ level):</b> Will take action on each document forwarded to such users. They will either approve and forward to other Railway user or return the document back to RVNL with observations or approval. The documents can also be forwarded to other Railway user without approval. Will be able to generate different types of reports for documents lying in that zone and in any division of that zone. Will have access to all documents and details pertaining to that zone and divisions of that zone and concerned PIU(s). After approval of the document from all concerned zonal HQ officers, document will be returned back to RVNL for marking it as finally approved and close the log.</td></tr><tr ><td> 8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Railway User (Railway Board level):</b> Will only monitor position and will be able to generate different types of reports. Will have access to all documents and details available in the system.</td></tr><tr ><td> 9)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Users of Other Organization (e.g. NHAI, MCL etc):</b> Will not have any access to the system as such users are created to show documents pending with such organizations and to log time taken in approvals. The movement of document to and receipt of approved document back from such users will only be registered in the system by RVNL user only so that a notional log is created for reporting purpose.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Master Data</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>This contains the details of base/master data i.e. Zones, Divisions, RVNL PIUs, Other Organizations, Departments, Designations, Project Types and Document Types.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>All the above details can be added/modified by System-Admin only.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Project Creation</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Local-Admin can create a new project and can also update information of an existing project, if no document has been created in that particular project. However, details like jurisdiction details and package wise nos. of drawings/documents required to be created/approved can be updated later also without any restrictions.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Jurisdiction Details</b> for a project are entered in form of Major section, from km & to km details of the project jurisdiction. In case project is spread over more than one major section, add major section button can be used to add a new row. Similarly major section wise Station Details (name and km) are also to be entered to show all the stations in the jurisdictions of the project. Add Station button can be used to add a new station row. Upto 10 major section rows and 100 station rows can be created.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Along with details like zone, division, project director, the nos. of documents/drawing required to be created/approved for each document type (i.e. ESP, Bridge GAD etc) for each package is to be entered. </td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>System Admin/Local Admin can only update information of any project, he can also change zone if document within that package is not created.</td></tr><tr ><td> 5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Local Admin can add and remove packages. A project can have maximum 15 packages. A package can only be removed, if no document of that particular package has been forwarded for approval of railway.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Document Creation & Approval</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>A document is created for a particular project by PIU level User of RVNL and is assigned to different users of MOR(Ministry of Railways) as per requirement of that particular document. RVNL user will also earmark permissible time in days for each Railway user for his scrutiny and approval. This time limit will be used for working out delays and also sending alerts. After creation, the document will be forwarded to a Railway user. The document can also be shown forwarded to users of other Organizations to keep log of movement and map delays.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Location Details for a particular document are to be filled to indicate its geographical jurisdiction. This will require filling up of details likeMajor Section,  From KM & to KM  for document type having jurisdiction over a length of section i.e. index plan & section or Major Section &  KM for document type belonging to a particular location/ chainage i.e. Bridge GAD or Major Section & Station for document type belonging to particular station i.e. ESP. These details will be filled up within project jurisdiction details already filled and are having proper validation to prevent wrong entries.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>A Railway user can perform three actions on a document;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;i.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Forward With Approval - </b> User can approve the document and forward to other assigned/available Railway users or can also return the approved document to RVNL in case he happens to be last in approval chain.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ii.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Forward Without Approval - </b> Forward without approval to other assigned/ available Railway users to get it examined/re-examined for a particular issue.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;iii.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Return to RVNL -</b> Directly return to RVNL for compliance of certain observations.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Document information can be updated by RVNL user who has created it, if any changes are required except date of forward to Railways in case when it is already forwarded to Railway user.</td></tr><tr ><td> 5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Forwarding User-list can also be updated by Supervisor except that no changes can be made for the Railway user with whom the document is pending at that moment.</td></tr><tr ><td> 6)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>In case of no assignees list, that means users have not been created for that division and zone assigned to that document and contact the Local-Admin to get users of particular division/zone created.</td></tr><tr ><td> 7)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>After modification of the assignee list, RVNL user can forward the created document to particular created assignees list (only when the document has not been forwarded already) & you can change the dateof submission to railways at that time (not mandatory).</td></tr><tr ><td> 8)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>After approval of the document from all concerned divisional officers, document will be returned back to RVNL for submission to Zonal HQ (if required).<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Returned Tasks</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Documents which are returned back to RVNL will be visible to appropriate RVNL user (who created it) & he can again resubmit/forward it to Railway user or the other Organization. In case document has been returned with observations, it can be resubmitted to the same Railway user after necessary compliance or may be forwarded to any other Railway user.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>The documents returned as approved are shown in different color and that pending with other organization in different color.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>From Returned task tab, RVNL user can also forward (notional) a document to users of Other Organization like NHAI etc. and later register their approval after getting the document back physically.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Approved documents in Returned Task tab, can also be forwarded to Railway users in case approvals of some new user(s) is found necessary at this stage.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Document Final Approval</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Documents, which are approved from all users and returned back to RVNL user,   will be having green color button (enabled) and RVNL user can mark them as finally approved.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Documents, which are pending for approval or still not approved by all the users will be having grey color button (disabled) and RVNL user cannot mark them as finally approved.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Once a document is finally approved, it is not available on dashboards of any of RVNL/Railway users for further actions like forward, approval etc and can be seen only through reports.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>In exceptional cases, when it is required to be revived, System-Admin can reopen the document on request of the concerned RVNL user.</td></tr><tr ><td> 5)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>There is no option for deletion of a document and any document (garbage) wrongly created and not required to be used for seeking approval can be pulled back from Railway user (if forwarded) and then be shown as 'Finally Approved' to put the same in cold storage.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Pullback Documents</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>By selecting appropriate resources filter, RVNL User can pullback a document pending with any Railway user.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Selected document can be Pulledback & will be shown in Returned Task tab. This document will also be available for final approval.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Approved documents in Returned Task tab, can also be forwarded to Railway users in case approvals of some new user(s) is found necessary at this stage.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Alerts and Reminders</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>System has been designed to trigger automatic email/SMS alerts to Railway user when a document is being forwarded to him by RVNL user/another Railway user. This action will be real time basis.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>All the Railway users will automatically get a reminder email/SMS in case a document is not approved within the prescribed time period for that user. The time period shall be counted from date of submission/date of forward of document to that user as entered in the system. Such reminders will first be triggered by the system on the next day on completion of prescribed time period but excluding Saturdays and Sundays. Subsequent reminders will be triggered on weekly basis on every Monday.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>There is a provision of sending weekly position of documents to DRM of a division for documents pending with that division and delayed beyond a particular time limit i.e. 7 days. The position (in tabular form) will be sent by email weekly on every Monday. SMS alert will also be sent regarding this email.</td></tr><tr ><td> 4)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Similar there is a provision of sending weekly position of documents to GM of a zone for documents pending in the zonal HQ and delayed beyond a particular time limit i.e. 7 days and also documents pending with divisions of that zone and delayed beyond a particular time limit i.e. 30 days. The position (in tabular form) will be sent weekly on every Monday. SMS alert will also be sent regarding this email.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Reports</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Different types of Reports based on selected filters can be generated. The reports can then be printed or exported to local machine in PDF and Excel formats. For each document shown in the detailed report, log details for particular document can also be seen/printed/exported. The reports also have provision of sorting, search and record display control etc for fast and better retrieval of the required information.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>The reports can be filtered for 'Zone', 'Division', 'PIU', 'Project Type', 'Project', 'Document Type', 'documents submitted between  two dates', 'approved/ pending status', 'pending with particular Railway user', 'pending for more than a predefined number of days', 'pending with users of other organizations'. In addition, documents of a project can also be filtered for 'Km wise' or 'Station wise' stretch of location.</td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>There are basically five different types of reports generated by the system as given below;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Detailed Report:</b> In this report, detailed data for all documents is shown. Further details i.e. log /movement details from submission to Railways till final approval can also be seen for each document by clicking the 'Details' button. Reports are generated for documents meeting the selection/filter criteria selected in the report selection tab. For generating reports for documents belonging to particular stretch of the project, when a project is selected, location details (Km wise / Station wise) entry panel becomes visible and then data can be filled as filter criteria for the report. Filters can also be used for reports of the documents pending with a User (MOR/Other Organization) or pending for more than a pre-defined period in days. However, pending days filter will be enabled only when status filter is selected as 'Pending'. Filter selection is shown on the top of the report and then a table containing document wise details is shown.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><b>Summary Reports:</b></td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">On selection of this type of reports, time period entry panel becomes visible where 'x' & 'y' for three time periods can be entered as per user's choice to generate reports accordingly. The default values for 'x' and 'y' are 30 & 60 days respectively. Users can change these values as per choice. </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Such reports also show the document's list based on selection of particular project and specific location/stretch of the project.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">'Status', 'Railway User Id' & 'Under Approval for more than' filters are  disabled in all summary reports and 'Organization (other than Railway & RVNL)' filter is disabled for Project Specific Status Report.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Filter selection is shown on the top of the report and then a table containing document wise details is shown.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">The following types of Summary reports can be generated from the Reports tab;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;i.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Project Wise Summary Report:</b> This type of reports show project package wise summary position for following parameters;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents approved, </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Average time taken for approval by Railways, Other Organizations and RVNL.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents pending for approval with Railways, with other Organizations with breakup in three pre-set time periods (< x days, x to y days, > y days) </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents pending for compliance with RVNL with breakup in three pre-set time periods (< x days, x to y days, > y days) </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">The nos. of documents figures in the report are hyperlinked to detailed report containing only documents leading to that figures with further button link for log details for each document.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ii.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Department Wise Summary Report:</b> This type of report shows department wise summary position for divisions under different zones. Zonal Headquarter is also shown separately under division column. RVNL is shown as a department of division separately for documents pertaining to that division. This summary report shows following parameters;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents cleared by each department of division/HQ</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Average time taken for clearance by each department (by all user of that departments)  </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents pending for approval with users of each department with breakup in three pre-set time periods (< x days, x to y days, > y days) </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">The nos. of documents figures in the report are hyperlinked to detailed report containing only documents leading to that figures with further button link for log details for each document.</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;iii.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Project Specific Status Report:</b> This type of report shows document type wise summary position for each package of a selected project. User has to select a specific project for this report. This type of report shows package wise document details and location type filter is not available.  This summary report shows package wise and document type wise report on the following parameters;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents required </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents prepared</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents approved</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents pending for approval</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">The nos. of documents figures in the report are hyperlinked to detailed report containing only documents leading to that figures with further button link for log details for each document.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;iv.&nbsp;</td><td><b>Monthwise Summary Report:</b> This type of report shows month wise summary position for nos. of documents submitted and nos. of documents approved during last 12 months. The last month is the current month. This type of report allows project wise filtering and location type filter is not available.  This summary report shows month wise report on the following parameters;</td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents submitted </td></tr><tr ><td> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;#</td><td style=\"padding-left:30px;\">Nos. of documents approved</td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Forget Password</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>In case a user forgets his password, he should contact the System-Admin/Local-Admin to reset his password.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>A user can also change his password any time using his current password.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Help</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>System provides for on board 'Help' tab to different types of users.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>Detailed process flow is also additionally available on click of a button.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Contact us</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>For any user profile changes or password reset, Railway users in zonal HQ and divisions or PIU level RVNL users can contact Local-Admin of PIU of RVNL linked to particular Railway Zone. A table gives contact details of Local Admins of various RVNL PIUs and zones connected to them.</td></tr><tr ><td> 2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>For any user profile changes or password reset, Local-Admins of RVNL PIUs, Railway Board users  and RVNL Corporate Office users can contact System Administrator at RVNL Corporate Office whose contact details are given on the page. </td></tr><tr ><td> 3)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>For any technical problem in the system, users can contact their local admin or system admin.<br><br></td></tr><tr ><td class=\"test\" style=\"font-weight:bold\" colspan=\"2\"> <h8 >Themes</h8></td></tr><tr ><td> 1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>You can set a colour theme (out of four themes - Brown, Blue, Green & Magenta buttons on top right corner of your dashboard page) to the portal. The theme with larger theme icon is currently active. You can change the theme by clicking on any other theme button/icon. <br><br></td></tr></table>\r\n");
      out.write("<div style=\"text-align:center\"><input type=\"reset\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" value=\"Close\" onclick = \"javascript:self.close();\" />\r\n");
